1
00:00:08,208 --> 00:00:09,333
[PHOENIX]
My name is Phoenix Wright.

2
00:00:09,416 --> 00:00:11,375
And I'm a defense attorney.

3
00:00:11,458 --> 00:00:13,500
No matter the odds,
it's my job to stand up

4
00:00:13,583 --> 00:00:15,916
for those who have no one
else in their corner.

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:18,791
I'll do whatever it
takes to fight for the truth!

6
00:00:21,541 --> 00:00:23,541
[VOICE]
The time is 1 AM.

7
00:00:30,416 --> 00:00:32,291
There goes the
deadline that we were given.

8
00:00:32,375 --> 00:00:33,916
And the jewel's still
resting safe and sound

9
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:35,166
under lock and key.

10
00:00:35,250 --> 00:00:36,416
Bet he got scared
'cause he knew

11
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:39,166
ol' "big" Dick Gumshoe
and his crew was here.

12
00:00:45,916 --> 00:00:49,541
Aw, for cryin' out loud!
We've been bamboozled!

13
00:00:49,625 --> 00:00:51,291
[MASK laughs]

14
00:00:51,375 --> 00:00:53,291
[BOTH gasp]

15
00:00:53,375 --> 00:00:55,166
[MASK]
Sorry to get your hopes up.

16
00:00:55,250 --> 00:00:57,125
Those are the breaks.

17
00:00:57,208 --> 00:00:59,166
Mask DeMasque,
the phantom thief!

18
00:00:59,250 --> 00:01:00,375
We shall meet again, detective.

19
00:01:00,458 --> 00:01:03,166
When the moon
is bright and full.

20
00:01:03,250 --> 00:01:07,083
[MASK laughs]

21
00:02:42,583 --> 00:02:47,125
[PHOENIX hums]

22
00:02:47,208 --> 00:02:49,791
Are you seriously
cleaning the toilet again?

23
00:02:49,875 --> 00:02:52,583
No work, so I gotta
make myself useful somehow.

24
00:02:52,666 --> 00:02:56,708
Oh, wow, that's just pathetic.
Hope I don't end up like you.

25
00:02:56,791 --> 00:02:58,833
[PHOENIX growls]
You might.

26
00:02:58,916 --> 00:03:00,458
Especially if you slack off
on your training.

27
00:03:00,541 --> 00:03:01,791
[MAYA]
Get off my case.

28
00:03:01,875 --> 00:03:04,333
I'm way too busy working
to train right now.

29
00:03:04,416 --> 00:03:05,583
[PHOENIX] Busy working
on "becoming one"

30
00:03:05,666 --> 00:03:06,875
with the couch, right?

31
00:03:06,958 --> 00:03:09,083
Hey! I know you've been
playing games all night

32
00:03:09,166 --> 00:03:10,458
when, in reality,

33
00:03:10,541 --> 00:03:12,208
you should be trying to
gather up some new clients.

34
00:03:12,291 --> 00:03:15,208
[PEARL] Oh, you two having
one of your couple's spats?

35
00:03:15,291 --> 00:03:16,375
[BOTH gasp]

36
00:03:16,458 --> 00:03:18,708
My gosh. You're so cute!

37
00:03:18,791 --> 00:03:20,250
--[MAYA] Pearls?
--[PHOENIX] Pearl!

38
00:03:22,458 --> 00:03:25,541
Glad you're here, but what
brings you into the city?

39
00:03:25,625 --> 00:03:27,625
Heh. I thought that
Mystic Maya would've

40
00:03:27,708 --> 00:03:29,041
told you about it by now.

41
00:03:29,125 --> 00:03:30,166
Ah?

42
00:03:31,333 --> 00:03:33,500
"Kurain Village treasures"? Huh.

43
00:03:33,583 --> 00:03:36,208
Yup! Straight from me
and Pearl's hometown!

44
00:03:36,291 --> 00:03:38,291
The exhibition doesn't
actually get started until

45
00:03:38,375 --> 00:03:40,000
next week, but the
promoter was nice enough

46
00:03:40,083 --> 00:03:42,708
to give us some VIP passes
so we could go early.

47
00:03:42,791 --> 00:03:44,041
VIPs!

48
00:03:44,125 --> 00:03:46,958
So I decided to go all out
and dress extra fancy.

49
00:03:47,041 --> 00:03:48,375
Whattaya think?

50
00:03:48,458 --> 00:03:50,500
[PHOENIX] That's, like,
the only thing you ever wear.

51
00:03:50,583 --> 00:03:52,541
Yep, good 'ol Maya Fey.

52
00:03:52,625 --> 00:03:54,750
She's the younger sister
of my friend and mentor,

53
00:03:54,833 --> 00:03:56,833
the late Mia Fey.

54
00:03:56,916 --> 00:03:59,708
I met her a couple of
years ago, and even defended her

55
00:03:59,791 --> 00:04:03,458
when she was falsely accused
of Mia's tragic murder.

56
00:04:03,541 --> 00:04:04,833
They're from Kurain Village,

57
00:04:04,916 --> 00:04:07,791
home of the mysterious
Spirit Channeling technique.

58
00:04:07,875 --> 00:04:10,250
Maya's the daughter
of the Kurain School's master

59
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:13,083
and is training to become
a spirit medium herself.

60
00:04:13,166 --> 00:04:14,875
Of course, the
precocious little girl

61
00:04:14,958 --> 00:04:16,375
is Pearl Fey.

62
00:04:16,458 --> 00:04:17,583
She's Maya's cousin,

63
00:04:17,666 --> 00:04:20,583
and also a young spirit
medium in training.

64
00:04:20,666 --> 00:04:22,833
The promo poster
looks better than I'd hoped!

65
00:04:22,916 --> 00:04:25,208
They even got a great picture
of the sacred urn!

66
00:04:25,291 --> 00:04:27,666
[gasps]
I still feel bad.

67
00:04:27,750 --> 00:04:28,875
First, I broke the urn,

68
00:04:28,958 --> 00:04:30,791
and then I put it back
together all wrong.

69
00:04:30,875 --> 00:04:32,375
It's fine!

70
00:04:32,458 --> 00:04:34,416
I'm sure Mystic Ami's just happy
to know that you did the best

71
00:04:34,500 --> 00:04:36,708
that you possibly could!

72
00:04:36,791 --> 00:04:38,958
[PHOENIX] A year ago,
while we were investigating

73
00:04:39,041 --> 00:04:42,208
a murder case in Kurain Village,
little Pearl accidentally

74
00:04:42,291 --> 00:04:45,791
shattered the sacred urn that
contains the spirit of Ami Fey,

75
00:04:45,875 --> 00:04:48,208
the school's founder
and protector.

76
00:04:48,291 --> 00:04:49,500
But by breaking the urn,

77
00:04:49,583 --> 00:04:51,791
she unwittingly broke
the case as well.

78
00:04:53,791 --> 00:04:54,958
[REPORTER 2A]
In other news,

79
00:04:55,041 --> 00:04:56,375
police are searching for
clues after a theft from

80
00:04:56,458 --> 00:04:58,916
the upcoming treasure exhibit
at Lordly Tailor hall.

81
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,333
[MAYA]
Eh?

82
00:05:00,416 --> 00:05:03,375
The rare item stolen, an urn,
was taken last night.

83
00:05:03,458 --> 00:05:04,875
[gasps]

84
00:05:04,958 --> 00:05:06,416
[REPORTER 2A] Authorities
believe the heist was the work

85
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:10,125
of the notorious, so-called
"Phantom thief," Mask DeMasque.

86
00:05:10,208 --> 00:05:11,791
Masque the Mask?

87
00:05:11,875 --> 00:05:13,291
A criminal mastermind.

88
00:05:13,375 --> 00:05:15,416
A thief that targets
rare treasures.

89
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:18,791
He's like a ghost, and
no one knows who he really is!

90
00:05:18,875 --> 00:05:19,916
Hence the name.

91
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:22,416
I just can't
believe they stole it.

92
00:05:22,500 --> 00:05:24,666
That urn is sacred to us.

93
00:05:24,750 --> 00:05:27,250
Oh, no!

94
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:42,875
Ahh...

95
00:05:42,958 --> 00:05:44,500
The bitterness
stimulates the tongue,

96
00:05:44,583 --> 00:05:46,916
while the richness
warms the throat!

97
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:51,083
Exquisite. Life is
about stimulation.

98
00:05:51,166 --> 00:05:54,291
And not going through all the
highs and lows it can offer.

99
00:05:54,375 --> 00:05:55,791
Leaves one sour.

100
00:05:55,875 --> 00:05:58,583
We're on the scene at the
Lordly Tailor exhibit hall...

101
00:05:58,666 --> 00:06:01,708
Tch. This ought
to be a real party.

102
00:06:07,625 --> 00:06:12,541
[MAYA growls] Stupid jerk!
I mean, who would steal our urn?

103
00:06:12,625 --> 00:06:13,625
All right, then.

104
00:06:13,708 --> 00:06:15,041
Since it's our treasure
that was stolen,

105
00:06:15,125 --> 00:06:16,458
it's up to you to
find the thief!

106
00:06:16,541 --> 00:06:18,375
--[gasps]
--Yeah, she's right!

107
00:06:18,458 --> 00:06:20,875
The only person who
can get it back is you!

108
00:06:20,958 --> 00:06:23,125
But I'm just a defense
attorney, not a private eye.

109
00:06:23,208 --> 00:06:25,166
Hey! Don't start making excuses!

110
00:06:25,250 --> 00:06:27,541
A real hero will gladly do
whatever it takes to help out

111
00:06:27,625 --> 00:06:29,250
his beloved maiden in need!

112
00:06:29,333 --> 00:06:30,375
[PHOENIX]
Man, I can't win against

113
00:06:30,458 --> 00:06:32,791
Pearl's fairy tale
ideas about romance.

114
00:06:32,875 --> 00:06:34,458
But how are we gonna get inside?

115
00:06:34,541 --> 00:06:36,500
It won't be easy.
[gasps]

116
00:06:36,583 --> 00:06:38,291
[MAYA]
Excuse me. Coming through.

117
00:06:38,375 --> 00:06:40,625
Hold it, lady!
No outsiders allowed!

118
00:06:40,708 --> 00:06:42,458
I am not an outsider, pal!

119
00:06:42,541 --> 00:06:45,750
I even have my lawyer and
my cousin here with me!

120
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:47,541
[PHOENIX] Why would
having a cousin matter?

121
00:06:47,625 --> 00:06:48,833
[ANDREWS]
Mr. Wright!

122
00:06:48,916 --> 00:06:51,375
[gasps]
Ms. Andrews!

123
00:06:52,708 --> 00:06:55,583
[ANDREWS] Thanks again
for your help last time.

124
00:06:55,666 --> 00:06:57,458
I was just doing my job, ma'am.

125
00:06:57,541 --> 00:07:00,083
Anyway, I didn't expect
to see you here.

126
00:07:00,166 --> 00:07:01,750
[PHOENIX]
This is Ms. Adrian Andrews.

127
00:07:01,833 --> 00:07:04,083
Former talent agent
and a crucial figure in

128
00:07:04,166 --> 00:07:05,875
the Nickel Samurai case.

129
00:07:08,208 --> 00:07:10,000
[ANDREWS] Things have changed a
lot for me since the last time

130
00:07:10,083 --> 00:07:11,458
we saw each other.

131
00:07:11,541 --> 00:07:14,375
I'm now head of events and
promotion for Lordly Tailor.

132
00:07:16,666 --> 00:07:18,833
I am truly sorry
about all of this.

133
00:07:18,916 --> 00:07:20,333
I've failed you.

134
00:07:20,416 --> 00:07:21,750
[gasps]

135
00:07:21,833 --> 00:07:24,291
Your precious urn was
stolen from right under my nose.

136
00:07:24,375 --> 00:07:27,666
I take full responsibility.
But, I promise--

137
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:30,375
No! The person responsible
is the phantom thief!

138
00:07:30,458 --> 00:07:31,833
[gasps]

139
00:07:31,916 --> 00:07:35,083
We know this is the last
thing you wanted to happen.

140
00:07:35,166 --> 00:07:38,125
Thanks for that. And I'll
try to make things right.

141
00:07:38,208 --> 00:07:40,291
You can start by telling us
everything you know

142
00:07:40,375 --> 00:07:41,666
about the crime.

143
00:07:41,750 --> 00:07:43,750
Well, first off, the phantom
thief himself sent us

144
00:07:43,833 --> 00:07:46,291
a calling card of
sorts ten days ago.

145
00:07:46,375 --> 00:07:47,500
[PHOENIX]
What did it say?

146
00:07:47,583 --> 00:07:48,958
[ANDREWS] That he was
planning on stealing

147
00:07:49,041 --> 00:07:52,083
the most valuable piece in
the Kurain Village exhibit.

148
00:07:52,166 --> 00:07:54,333
Guess the urn's more
valuable than it looks, huh?

149
00:07:54,416 --> 00:07:56,875
That urn has Mystic
Ami's spirit inside of it,

150
00:07:56,958 --> 00:07:58,708
which makes it
unbelievably valuable!

151
00:07:58,791 --> 00:08:00,125
Hard to believe.

152
00:08:00,208 --> 00:08:01,750
We had an appraisal
done that discovered

153
00:08:01,833 --> 00:08:04,041
it had zero monetary value.

154
00:08:04,125 --> 00:08:05,458
Zero...?

155
00:08:05,541 --> 00:08:07,333
But I did my best to
polish it and make it look

156
00:08:07,416 --> 00:08:08,791
like it was worth millions!

157
00:08:08,875 --> 00:08:11,583
I think it's quite a beautiful
work of art, honestly!

158
00:08:11,666 --> 00:08:14,208
Aw... Poor Mystic Ami...

159
00:08:14,291 --> 00:08:16,500
Oh, but of course
money isn't everything!

160
00:08:16,583 --> 00:08:19,166
You simply can't put
a price on historical value.

161
00:08:19,250 --> 00:08:21,125
Not to mention on a soul!

162
00:08:21,208 --> 00:08:23,458
I misspoke! Please forgive me!

163
00:08:29,791 --> 00:08:31,500
[ANDREWS]
This is where it was stored.

164
00:08:31,583 --> 00:08:33,166
So it was in here?

165
00:08:33,250 --> 00:08:35,208
Doesn't really look like
a crime scene to me.

166
00:08:35,291 --> 00:08:37,875
[GUMSHOE]
Fancy seeing you again.

167
00:08:37,958 --> 00:08:39,416
[PHOENIX]
Detective Gumshoe!

168
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:41,708
It's nutty. What are the odds?

169
00:08:41,791 --> 00:08:44,083
How are you there
every single time?

170
00:08:44,166 --> 00:08:46,583
Aren't you a homicide detective?

171
00:08:46,666 --> 00:08:50,416
Look! Over there!
It's Mystic Ami!

172
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:54,000
Oh. Very impressive.

173
00:08:54,083 --> 00:08:56,083
But what is she
doing over there...?

174
00:08:56,166 --> 00:08:57,583
Something wrong, Ms. Andrews?

175
00:08:57,666 --> 00:08:59,791
[ANDREWS]
Ah? Oh, no.

176
00:08:59,875 --> 00:09:02,666
But the little girl is right,
that's a statue of Ami Fey,

177
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:04,166
the founder of the
Kurain School's

178
00:09:04,250 --> 00:09:05,875
spirit channeling technique.

179
00:09:05,958 --> 00:09:08,541
It was delivered
yesterday afternoon.

180
00:09:08,625 --> 00:09:10,250
Just think about it,
Mystic Maya,

181
00:09:10,333 --> 00:09:11,916
someday, you'll take over
the clan and become

182
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,791
the master of Kurain.
Isn't it cool?

183
00:09:13,875 --> 00:09:15,833
Uh. Oh, yeah!

184
00:09:15,916 --> 00:09:19,125
My, my, might this be
a meeting of the minds?

185
00:09:19,208 --> 00:09:20,125
[GROUP]
Hmm?

186
00:09:20,208 --> 00:09:23,208
[LUKE chuckles]

187
00:09:23,291 --> 00:09:25,083
Wait. Who's this?

188
00:09:25,166 --> 00:09:27,625
Welcome to my little soiree.

189
00:09:27,708 --> 00:09:29,583
A Feast of Chaos!

190
00:09:31,666 --> 00:09:36,916
[LUKE chuckles] I see it as
clearly as the nose on my face.

191
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:38,583
You do? But what is it?

192
00:09:38,666 --> 00:09:40,125
[LUKE]
Zvarri!

193
00:09:40,208 --> 00:09:43,583
And once again, the truth so
elegantly reveals itself to me.

194
00:09:43,666 --> 00:09:47,000
I see a lawyer
and a spirit medium.

195
00:09:47,083 --> 00:09:49,375
Both but beginners in their
particular professions.

196
00:09:49,458 --> 00:09:52,000
Say what? How could you
know all that just by looking?

197
00:09:52,083 --> 00:09:53,958
[LUKE] How, you ask?
For a skeptical mind,

198
00:09:54,041 --> 00:09:56,291
"how" is as pertinent
a question as "why."

199
00:09:56,375 --> 00:09:59,208
I am a tried and true
traveler of both time and space.

200
00:09:59,291 --> 00:10:01,541
As well as a man who
drifts through dreams.

201
00:10:01,625 --> 00:10:04,250
I might call him a lot of
things, but not any of those.

202
00:10:04,333 --> 00:10:06,208
He's just trying
to put on a show.

203
00:10:06,291 --> 00:10:10,125
The poster for the exhibition
had a little blurb about you.

204
00:10:10,208 --> 00:10:11,625
And the attorney's
badge I'm wearing

205
00:10:11,708 --> 00:10:13,666
is kind of a giveaway.

206
00:10:13,750 --> 00:10:15,166
I am Luke Atmey!

207
00:10:15,250 --> 00:10:17,625
A man unto whom some
have bestowed the title.

208
00:10:17,708 --> 00:10:19,208
Ace Detective.

209
00:10:19,291 --> 00:10:20,500
Sounds familiar.

210
00:10:20,583 --> 00:10:21,791
I've seen him on the news,

211
00:10:21,875 --> 00:10:24,000
he was on the "Great People
in Town" segment.

212
00:10:24,083 --> 00:10:25,291
[PHOENIX]
Is that really even a thing?

213
00:10:25,375 --> 00:10:26,750
Seems there's
a plethora of things

214
00:10:26,833 --> 00:10:29,583
you don't know, counselor!
It's quite strange.

215
00:10:29,666 --> 00:10:32,000
Usually, the tales of my
investigative prowess

216
00:10:32,083 --> 00:10:33,875
precede me wherever I go!

217
00:10:33,958 --> 00:10:35,291
Very well.

218
00:10:35,375 --> 00:10:36,958
Please, allow me the pleasure
of enlightening you on

219
00:10:37,041 --> 00:10:39,000
the topic of myself!

220
00:10:39,083 --> 00:10:40,958
If this has not permeated
the particular rock

221
00:10:41,041 --> 00:10:43,166
you're living under,
there is a yin and yang

222
00:10:43,250 --> 00:10:46,375
of good and evil in this city!
I am on the side of light,

223
00:10:46,458 --> 00:10:49,041
while Mask DeMasque
dwells in darkness!

224
00:10:49,125 --> 00:10:51,916
And when his shadow
enshrouds all under its pall,

225
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:54,458
I shall turn a spotlight on
that ghostly figure

226
00:10:54,541 --> 00:10:56,625
and expose him to the world!

227
00:10:56,708 --> 00:10:58,875
You get the feeling his
voice is his favorite sound?

228
00:10:58,958 --> 00:11:00,458
[PHOENIX]
Mm-hmm.

229
00:11:00,541 --> 00:11:02,333
[LUKE] I have been personally
pursuing the pseudonymed phantom

230
00:11:02,416 --> 00:11:05,041
since the inception of his
immorality, and thwarted

231
00:11:05,125 --> 00:11:08,125
his latest loathsome larceny
armed only with my intellect

232
00:11:08,208 --> 00:11:10,875
and insatiable
inquisitive ingenuity!

233
00:11:10,958 --> 00:11:13,416
One could argue that
we're two sides of the same coin

234
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:17,041
buying our way into history.
A rivalry for the ages!

235
00:11:17,125 --> 00:11:19,958
And last night, at 1 AM,
we stood face to face

236
00:11:20,041 --> 00:11:23,333
in the bowels of this building,
engaged in brilliant battle!

237
00:11:23,416 --> 00:11:25,625
[PHOENIX]
So it was 1 AM. Wait.

238
00:11:25,708 --> 00:11:27,416
You mean to tell us that you
were on the premises

239
00:11:27,500 --> 00:11:29,041
when the robbery took place?

240
00:11:29,125 --> 00:11:31,041
But of course. You see...

241
00:11:31,125 --> 00:11:33,500
Wherever DeMasque dares
to tread, be assured, Atmey

242
00:11:33,583 --> 00:11:35,166
has already set an elegant trap.

243
00:11:35,250 --> 00:11:37,625
Ah. But the trap was
not elegant enough.

244
00:11:37,708 --> 00:11:40,750
Actually, I allowed him
to escape filled with fantasy.

245
00:11:40,833 --> 00:11:42,125
An illusion of victory.

246
00:11:42,208 --> 00:11:44,916
But still, you were
on guard last night. Why?

247
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:48,500
The gentlewoman solicited
my services as sentry.

248
00:11:48,583 --> 00:11:51,375
Twenty days ago, in fact,
which was ten full days,

249
00:11:51,458 --> 00:11:53,750
before DeMasque declared
his dastardly designs

250
00:11:53,833 --> 00:11:55,125
to dame Andrews.

251
00:11:55,208 --> 00:11:57,541
She hired you before the
calling card was delivered?

252
00:11:57,625 --> 00:11:59,208
I did. I couldn't
shake the feeling

253
00:11:59,291 --> 00:12:00,791
something bad was
going to happen.

254
00:12:00,875 --> 00:12:03,250
And her premonition
proved to be prescient.

255
00:12:03,333 --> 00:12:05,166
The calling card
arrived soon after.

256
00:12:05,250 --> 00:12:06,291
Indeed!

257
00:12:06,375 --> 00:12:07,958
And since I am an Ace Detective,

258
00:12:08,041 --> 00:12:11,083
I expertly arranged an elegant
trap to ensnare the thief.

259
00:12:11,166 --> 00:12:12,666
If you knew something
was gonna happen,

260
00:12:12,750 --> 00:12:14,541
why not go to the
police for help?

261
00:12:14,625 --> 00:12:17,625
Feh. Like I need backup from
that bumbling bunch of boobs.

262
00:12:17,708 --> 00:12:19,875
Why, you-- What did you say?

263
00:12:19,958 --> 00:12:21,125
Well, previously...

264
00:12:21,208 --> 00:12:23,125
...I personally pried
a priceless possession

265
00:12:23,208 --> 00:12:24,708
from the prowling purloiner.

266
00:12:24,791 --> 00:12:26,708
The masked marauder's
mischief making is matched

267
00:12:26,791 --> 00:12:28,791
only by my meticulous mind.

268
00:12:28,875 --> 00:12:30,750
Meanwhile, you metropolitan
meatheads missed

269
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:33,666
the mark on Mask
DeMasque's malfeasance.

270
00:12:33,750 --> 00:12:35,666
[GUMSHOE growls]

271
00:12:35,750 --> 00:12:36,958
So, counselor.

272
00:12:37,041 --> 00:12:38,875
Am I correct in my
characterization that

273
00:12:38,958 --> 00:12:41,500
you're committed to
capturing this caped criminal?

274
00:12:41,583 --> 00:12:42,833
Oh, we'll get 'im!

275
00:12:42,916 --> 00:12:44,625
I won't let this phantom
clown get away with taking

276
00:12:44,708 --> 00:12:45,875
Mystic Ami's urn!

277
00:12:45,958 --> 00:12:47,250
[LUKE]
Positively perfect.

278
00:12:47,333 --> 00:12:49,083
Please proceed with
perusing the perimeter

279
00:12:49,166 --> 00:12:51,041
whist I explore elsewhere.

280
00:12:51,125 --> 00:12:52,750
We shall catch up counselor.

281
00:12:52,833 --> 00:12:54,250
Happiest of hunting.

282
00:12:54,333 --> 00:12:55,666
[PHOENIX gruntz]

283
00:12:55,750 --> 00:12:57,541
That tool's a ton to take.

284
00:12:57,625 --> 00:13:00,125
He'd better start
respecting my authority.

285
00:13:00,208 --> 00:13:03,166
[phone rings]

286
00:13:03,250 --> 00:13:04,500
Yeah?

287
00:13:04,583 --> 00:13:06,083
[MAYA]
Hmm?

288
00:13:06,166 --> 00:13:09,666
[GUMSHOE] What? Mask DeMasque
really just turned himself in?

289
00:13:09,750 --> 00:13:10,958
[BOTH gasp]

290
00:13:14,458 --> 00:13:16,041
[GUMSHOE]
Sit tight, folks.

291
00:13:16,125 --> 00:13:19,041
The guards are gonna be bringing
him over in just a second.

292
00:13:19,125 --> 00:13:21,166
I don't think that I've
ever seen you this happy.

293
00:13:21,250 --> 00:13:22,541
It's a great day!

294
00:13:22,625 --> 00:13:24,333
We got our criminal
and that weird detective

295
00:13:24,416 --> 00:13:26,375
can go suck an egg!

296
00:13:26,458 --> 00:13:29,375
I'm gonna go start typing
up the report, see ya!

297
00:13:29,458 --> 00:13:30,958
Let's keep up
this winning streak!

298
00:13:31,041 --> 00:13:34,166
Since he surrendered himself,
does it really count as a win?

299
00:13:34,250 --> 00:13:36,041
Duh! Of course it's a win!

300
00:13:36,125 --> 00:13:37,791
Why are you so worked up, Maya?

301
00:13:37,875 --> 00:13:39,666
It should be completely
obvious why,

302
00:13:39,750 --> 00:13:41,083
because we're the victims!

303
00:13:41,166 --> 00:13:43,166
--Yeah, I guess so.
-[RON] Hey, there.

304
00:13:43,250 --> 00:13:44,875
Since we're always
doing murder cases,

305
00:13:44,958 --> 00:13:46,916
I usually think of the victims
as dead people and

306
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:48,583
that's super upsetting to me!

307
00:13:48,666 --> 00:13:50,000
[RON]
Excuse me.

308
00:13:50,083 --> 00:13:52,250
Wait, we gotta get the urn
back for Poor Mystic Ami!

309
00:13:52,333 --> 00:13:55,500
In case you haven't noticed,
I'm talkin' over here!

310
00:13:55,583 --> 00:13:56,958
Oh, sorry about that!

311
00:13:57,041 --> 00:13:58,208
Someone's there?

312
00:13:58,291 --> 00:13:59,541
Is that the guy?

313
00:13:59,625 --> 00:14:02,166
Excuse me. But my
name is Ron DeLite.

314
00:14:02,250 --> 00:14:04,875
And, uh... I'm also
known as Mask DeMasque.

315
00:14:04,958 --> 00:14:06,250
Or The Phantom Thief.

316
00:14:06,333 --> 00:14:08,541
Really? You're a
criminal mastermind?

317
00:14:08,625 --> 00:14:10,833
Oh, yeah! That's right!

318
00:14:10,916 --> 00:14:12,625
Or is it?

319
00:14:12,708 --> 00:14:15,250
I guess I can't really say
which one's a character

320
00:14:15,333 --> 00:14:16,458
and which one's me.

321
00:14:16,541 --> 00:14:18,750
He doesn't strike me
as the mysterious type.

322
00:14:18,833 --> 00:14:21,625
I mean... He talks like
he's trying to keep a secret.

323
00:14:21,708 --> 00:14:22,958
I know those looks.

324
00:14:23,041 --> 00:14:25,750
The last thing that I want
from you people is pity!

325
00:14:25,833 --> 00:14:27,625
Okay, sure, we get it!

326
00:14:27,708 --> 00:14:30,416
Hey! We need you give
us back that urn right now!

327
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:33,291
Yeah! I promise
I'll give it to you.

328
00:14:33,375 --> 00:14:36,416
But can I? Not good
to make promises I can't keep.

329
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:38,666
Yo! Speak up when
you're talkin' to me!

330
00:14:38,750 --> 00:14:39,958
I'm sorry about that!

331
00:14:40,041 --> 00:14:43,375
But I hate it when people yell!

332
00:14:43,458 --> 00:14:44,500
[GROUP]
Ah...

333
00:14:44,583 --> 00:14:49,791
[pants]
Look, uh... I, uh, kind of...

334
00:14:49,875 --> 00:14:51,958
I lost the Kurain urn, okay?

335
00:14:52,041 --> 00:14:52,958
Huh?

336
00:14:53,041 --> 00:14:56,375
You... What?

337
00:14:56,458 --> 00:14:58,166
You have gotta be kidding me!

338
00:14:58,250 --> 00:15:00,500
No, I wish this was
some kind of joke.

339
00:15:00,583 --> 00:15:02,375
But these things
happen all the time.

340
00:15:02,458 --> 00:15:04,375
You know, like leaving
your bag on a train.

341
00:15:04,458 --> 00:15:06,375
You left Mystic Ami's
urn on a train?

342
00:15:06,458 --> 00:15:07,833
And you were just
casually riding around

343
00:15:07,916 --> 00:15:09,166
in that getup?

344
00:15:09,250 --> 00:15:11,750
Now calm down! It's just
a hypothetical situation.

345
00:15:11,833 --> 00:15:13,125
Anyway...

346
00:15:13,208 --> 00:15:15,708
I'm so sorry!

347
00:15:15,791 --> 00:15:17,250
This guy...

348
00:15:17,333 --> 00:15:18,250
[DESIRÉE]
Ronnie!

349
00:15:18,333 --> 00:15:19,250
[GROUP gasps]

350
00:15:19,333 --> 00:15:20,750
[RON]
Oh, Dessie!

351
00:15:20,833 --> 00:15:22,333
Don't worry.

352
00:15:22,416 --> 00:15:24,541
I'm gonna do everything in my
power to get you outta there.

353
00:15:24,625 --> 00:15:25,833
I know you will, Dessie.

354
00:15:25,916 --> 00:15:28,375
So, uh...

355
00:15:28,458 --> 00:15:31,500
Please forgive me,
my name is Desirée DeLite.

356
00:15:31,583 --> 00:15:33,875
Desirée's my... My lovely wife.

357
00:15:33,958 --> 00:15:36,833
[gasps]
The phantom thief has a wife?

358
00:15:36,916 --> 00:15:39,333
My name is Phoenix Wright,
I'm a defense attorney.

359
00:15:39,416 --> 00:15:40,875
You don't say?

360
00:15:40,958 --> 00:15:42,708
Then, are you meeting with my
Ronnie because you're gonna

361
00:15:42,791 --> 00:15:43,875
take on his defense?

362
00:15:43,958 --> 00:15:45,916
Well, I haven't made up my mind.

363
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,125
Listen up, lady.

364
00:15:47,208 --> 00:15:49,416
We're the real victims
here, you got that?

365
00:15:49,500 --> 00:15:51,916
[gasps]
Wait a minute, are you Maya?

366
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,000
[MAYA]
Huh?

367
00:15:53,083 --> 00:15:54,791
Do you two know each other?

368
00:15:54,875 --> 00:15:56,625
She's on the poster. So.

369
00:15:56,708 --> 00:15:58,750
You're the Kurain
master's daughter, right?

370
00:15:58,833 --> 00:16:01,583
I didn't realize I was
starting to get so famous.

371
00:16:01,666 --> 00:16:03,958
Gosh, you're making me blush!

372
00:16:04,041 --> 00:16:06,333
[PHOENIX]
I thought you were a victim.

373
00:16:06,416 --> 00:16:09,541
[DESIRÉE] Ronnie did what?
No, I refuse to believe it!

374
00:16:09,625 --> 00:16:11,291
Why on earth would
he steal an urn?

375
00:16:11,375 --> 00:16:12,833
That's a tough question.

376
00:16:12,916 --> 00:16:15,791
But let me ask you something.
You know, don't you?

377
00:16:15,875 --> 00:16:17,625
About your husband
and Mask DeMasque?

378
00:16:17,708 --> 00:16:20,125
That's no secret.
He's pretty open about it.

379
00:16:20,208 --> 00:16:22,833
I mean, he's practically
DeMasque's biggest fan.

380
00:16:22,916 --> 00:16:24,041
He's a fan?

381
00:16:24,125 --> 00:16:26,583
Oh, definitely.
And he can get carried away.

382
00:16:26,666 --> 00:16:28,458
Wait, would you
clarify that, please?

383
00:16:28,541 --> 00:16:30,125
What do you mean
by "carried away"?

384
00:16:30,208 --> 00:16:31,875
He pretends he's
the phantom thief,

385
00:16:31,958 --> 00:16:33,833
and sometimes,
it's like he believes it.

386
00:16:33,916 --> 00:16:35,666
It's kooky, but so adorable.

387
00:16:35,750 --> 00:16:36,833
[PHOENIX]
Ah...

388
00:16:36,916 --> 00:16:39,208
Ronnie's timid. Always has been.

389
00:16:39,291 --> 00:16:41,625
So. DeMasque is like his hero.

390
00:16:41,708 --> 00:16:44,958
His hero? But the
phantom thief is a bad guy!

391
00:16:45,041 --> 00:16:46,458
[DESIRÉE chuckles]
Anyway.

392
00:16:46,541 --> 00:16:48,916
If Ronnie had stolen the urn,
wouldn't he still have it?

393
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:49,958
I'd think so.

394
00:16:50,041 --> 00:16:52,458
Well. Yeah.
That would make sense.

395
00:16:52,541 --> 00:16:53,750
He is odd.

396
00:16:53,833 --> 00:16:55,916
But I would never let him
do anything illegal.

397
00:16:56,000 --> 00:16:58,375
Good to know.
I wouldn't think otherwise.

398
00:16:58,458 --> 00:17:00,250
I believe somebody
must've framed him

399
00:17:00,333 --> 00:17:01,458
for the robbery.

400
00:17:01,541 --> 00:17:02,833
Really?

401
00:17:02,916 --> 00:17:05,041
I realize it's
a lot to ask of you.

402
00:17:05,125 --> 00:17:07,833
But would you agree
to defend my husband?

403
00:17:07,916 --> 00:17:09,583
--Well...
--There's a lot more

404
00:17:09,666 --> 00:17:12,750
to this case than meets the eye,
I know it! Please!

405
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:15,125
I'm begging you!

406
00:17:15,208 --> 00:17:18,083
Mrs. DeLite.

407
00:17:18,166 --> 00:17:19,416
How's this sound?

408
00:17:19,500 --> 00:17:21,625
I'll consider it and start
a full investigation.

409
00:17:21,708 --> 00:17:22,625
Huh?

410
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:24,333
Seriously? Thank you.

411
00:17:24,416 --> 00:17:26,541
I truly appreciate your help!

412
00:17:26,625 --> 00:17:27,791
How could you...?

413
00:17:27,875 --> 00:17:30,541
[PEARL gasps, growls]

414
00:17:30,625 --> 00:17:33,416
I am very disappointed
in you, Mr. Nick!

415
00:17:33,500 --> 00:17:34,666
What did I do now?

416
00:17:34,750 --> 00:17:37,250
Don't play dumb!
You're gonna defend that thief!

417
00:17:37,333 --> 00:17:39,541
He stole our family's
legacy from us!

418
00:17:39,625 --> 00:17:41,833
But what if it turns out
that Ron DeLite isn't really

419
00:17:41,916 --> 00:17:43,125
Mask DeMasque after all?

420
00:17:43,208 --> 00:17:45,125
Oh, because his wife
said he was delusional?

421
00:17:45,208 --> 00:17:46,958
She was probably lying to us!

422
00:17:47,041 --> 00:17:49,083
Or she could
be telling us the truth.

423
00:17:49,166 --> 00:17:50,541
[gasps]

424
00:17:50,625 --> 00:17:52,083
[PEARL] I can't believe
you'd really defend that jerk

425
00:17:52,166 --> 00:17:56,000
after what he did to Mystic Ami.
It breaks my heart...

426
00:17:56,083 --> 00:17:58,041
I can never forgive you!

427
00:17:58,125 --> 00:17:59,166
[gasps]

428
00:17:59,250 --> 00:18:00,791
Hang on, Pearls!

429
00:18:04,166 --> 00:18:05,500
[MAYA whimpers]

430
00:18:11,375 --> 00:18:13,750
[PEARL]
Mystic Maya. I'm sorry.

431
00:18:13,833 --> 00:18:15,583
[MAYA]
Eh?

432
00:18:15,666 --> 00:18:18,125
You and Mr. Nick are
fighting because of me.

433
00:18:18,208 --> 00:18:21,125
[MAYA] Mm-mm. You didn't do
anything wrong, sweetie.

434
00:18:21,208 --> 00:18:23,333
But what if it turns out
that Ron DeLite isn't really

435
00:18:23,416 --> 00:18:25,083
Mask DeMasque after all?

436
00:18:25,166 --> 00:18:26,666
[MAYA sighs]

437
00:18:26,750 --> 00:18:28,791
So, what do you think
we should do now?

438
00:18:30,708 --> 00:18:33,416
Talk to her. We'll get
the whole story from Desirée.

439
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:34,958
Ah.

440
00:18:35,041 --> 00:18:38,208
I want to know more about Ron.
Does that sound good to you?

441
00:18:38,291 --> 00:18:40,125
[gasps]
Yeah.

442
00:18:45,041 --> 00:18:46,541
[PHOENIX]
Uh, hello?

443
00:18:46,625 --> 00:18:49,000
Hello? Is anybody here?

444
00:18:49,083 --> 00:18:50,791
[sighs]
Don't know where he is,

445
00:18:50,875 --> 00:18:52,583
but that guy is out to lunch.

446
00:18:52,666 --> 00:18:54,916
I was hoping to get more
info on Mask DeMasque.

447
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:56,708
but I guess it'll have to wait.

448
00:19:01,375 --> 00:19:03,791
[MASK laughs]

449
00:19:03,875 --> 00:19:05,625
Sorry to get your hopes up.

450
00:19:05,708 --> 00:19:07,291
Those are the breaks.

451
00:19:07,375 --> 00:19:09,666
So then. To what do
I owe this pleasure?

452
00:19:09,750 --> 00:19:12,541
Well, first off, sorry for
dropping in unannounced.

453
00:19:12,625 --> 00:19:14,833
It's cool. Without Ronnie here,

454
00:19:14,916 --> 00:19:17,583
my only company is all
these costumes and toys.

455
00:19:17,666 --> 00:19:19,083
There are a lot.

456
00:19:19,166 --> 00:19:20,833
It's wild.

457
00:19:20,916 --> 00:19:23,416
To say he's got an
obsession is an understatement.

458
00:19:23,500 --> 00:19:25,541
I don't know what to
do with him sometimes.

459
00:19:25,625 --> 00:19:27,458
Anyway. What do you two need?

460
00:19:27,541 --> 00:19:29,083
Well. I, uh...

461
00:19:29,166 --> 00:19:30,958
[tea kettle whistles]

462
00:19:31,041 --> 00:19:32,125
Hold on a second.

463
00:19:32,208 --> 00:19:33,458
I'll go pour us some tea.

464
00:19:33,541 --> 00:19:34,583
A-Ah...

465
00:19:37,666 --> 00:19:39,416
[PHOENIX]
I wanna see what's in there.

466
00:19:39,500 --> 00:19:41,708
No, that sounds like
something Maya would do.

467
00:19:41,791 --> 00:19:43,875
I can almost picture
her egging me on.

468
00:19:43,958 --> 00:19:45,500
Just open it up Nick!

469
00:19:45,583 --> 00:19:47,041
A little peek won't kill ya.

470
00:19:47,125 --> 00:19:49,708
[PHOENIX] No, that's not how
an attorney conducts himself!

471
00:19:49,791 --> 00:19:51,208
Don't be such a scaredy-cat!

472
00:19:51,291 --> 00:19:52,791
Now's your only chance!

473
00:19:52,875 --> 00:19:53,958
[PHOENIX groans]

474
00:19:59,291 --> 00:20:03,125
Yeah. Fine. Just a peek, then.

475
00:20:03,208 --> 00:20:04,583
All right, little Pearls.

476
00:20:04,666 --> 00:20:06,208
Time to get to sleuthin'!

477
00:20:06,291 --> 00:20:07,958
Yeah, okay.

478
00:20:08,041 --> 00:20:09,333
With all this crazy stuff here,

479
00:20:09,416 --> 00:20:12,166
this has gotta be the
phantom thief's hideout.

480
00:20:13,541 --> 00:20:14,791
[gasps, screams]

481
00:20:14,875 --> 00:20:16,291
[gasps]

482
00:20:17,416 --> 00:20:19,958
Oh, Mystic Maya, are you okay?

483
00:20:22,083 --> 00:20:23,375
Ah?

484
00:20:27,083 --> 00:20:29,125
--[doorbell rings]
--[DESIRÉE] Coming!

485
00:20:29,208 --> 00:20:30,291
[MAYA gasps]

486
00:20:30,375 --> 00:20:33,000
Thank you so much.
I really appreciate it.

487
00:20:33,083 --> 00:20:34,833
[gasps]
Why's he here?

488
00:20:38,958 --> 00:20:42,291
[PHOENIX] What is this?
Something smooth and hard.

489
00:20:42,375 --> 00:20:43,708
[gasps]

490
00:20:43,791 --> 00:20:45,791
Ahoy! Is anyone here?

491
00:20:45,875 --> 00:20:47,875
Counselor, this
is quite concerning.

492
00:20:47,958 --> 00:20:49,666
I'm flabbergasted to
find a friend of the law

493
00:20:49,750 --> 00:20:51,250
flagrantly ignoring it.

494
00:20:51,333 --> 00:20:53,750
Uh. I'm sorry about that.

495
00:20:53,833 --> 00:20:57,166
Right. I suppose your
shortage of scruples will be

496
00:20:57,250 --> 00:20:59,041
of service as you
stand on the side of that

497
00:20:59,125 --> 00:21:01,750
sinister scofflaw,
some call DeMasque.

498
00:21:01,833 --> 00:21:03,291
[PHOENIX]
Where did you hear that?

499
00:21:03,375 --> 00:21:05,333
I'll be there at the trial.

500
00:21:05,416 --> 00:21:08,083
Providing my perceptions
to the prosecution.

501
00:21:08,166 --> 00:21:10,166
